  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to avoid seeing spammy/junk/empty messages so that I can focus on the chat experience.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Enhancement\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*:  Status messages can be full of line feeds that create long empty messages.  Sometimes users take advantage of this to spam the chat and prevent other users from reading messages.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"322\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-05-18 at 4 41 48 pm\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/116099/40241089-62561e2a-5aba-11e8-8b44-35823ed2831f.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\nOther users have pasted dozens of long messages filling the chat window and slowing down the app.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"317\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-05-18 at 8 08 45 pm\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/116099/40250666-4c797c92-5ad7-11e8-9ea0-7650e2ce8d75.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nMessage are shown\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nSpammy messages can be shown\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\nStart a chat and insert lots of line endings.\r\nOr copy/paste crazy long messages.\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n\r\nSlack and some other apps prevent empty messages by trimming any trailing line endings or spacing. Eg if you enter \"hello \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\" slack will only send \"hello\".\r\n\r\nHowever a user could also do \"hello \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n hello \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\" and recreate the issue.  \r\n\r\nPossible solutions could be to limit consecutive line endings, or spaces. Or even limit the message length to a certain amount of characters.\r\n\r\n@VoR0220 Suggested only showing the first part of a long message, with an option for the user to expand for more.\r\n\r\nOther approaches could be adding a 'ban user' feature so that users could remove jerky users.",
